Select a data file from your local directory system and define the type of data in the file if appropriate.

A study is made up of one or more entries.  The depositor may define a name and type of study conducted and provide the entry(s) that compose the study.  If a study is not defined by the depositor it will be assumed that the entry is the only member of a study and information provided for the entry will be used to poplulate corresponding tags in the study section to produce the final entry.
Provide information that describes the entry.

The information in a reference for the current entry if available is entered here.  Additional citations referenced in other portions of the entry also can be entered. Select the publication type click on Save then complete the resulting section.
Provide a description of the molecular assembly studied including a complete list of the molecules that make up the assembly.

Subsystems of the complete molecular assembly may be defined using this section.
Enter a complete description for each unique molecule (entity) in the system studied.
Provide the natural source for all biopolymers studied.
Enter the source used to produce the biopolymers studied in this entry.

Enter the complete contents for each sample used in the study.  This includes buffers salts and additives such as DTT etc.
Provide each set of conditions used to collect the data listed in the entry.
Enter the measured purity of each unique biopolymer in the samples and define the method used to measure purity.
